title: Number of births in Sweden 2009 to 2019
summary: This line chart has an x axis representing Year and a y axis representing Number of births, with a total of 11 data points. The chart has 7 significant trends.
The longest trend is moderately positive which exists from 2014 to 2011.
Correspondingly, the next significant trend is moderately negative which exists from 2011 to 2009.
On the other hand, the next significant trend is slightly negative which exists from 2019 to 2018.
Contrarily, the next significant trend is moderately positive which exists from 2018 to 2017.
Similarly, the next significant trend is slightly negative which exists from 2017 to 2016.
But, the next significant trend is extremely positive which exists from 2016 to 2015.
Also, the next significant trend is moderately negative which exists from 2015 to 2014.
gold: During the period from 2009 to 2019 , the highest number of babies born in Sweden was in 2016 , when over 117 thousand births occurred . In 2019 , about 115 thousand babies were born in Sweden . Within the last decade , there were yearly more baby boys than baby girls being born .
